## 🔐 Environment Variables

Create a `.env.local` file at the project root with these keys:

```env
# AWS Bedrock (for AI Pitch Grader)
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_aws_access_key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_aws_secret_key
AWS_REGION=us-east-1

# Twilio (for WhatsApp)
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
TWILIO_WHATSAPP_NUMBER=whatsapp:+14155238886   # Sandbox number
```

> **Never commit `.env.local` to GitHub.** It is listed in `.gitignore`.

### How to get these keys:
- **AWS Bedrock**: [aws.amazon.com → IAM → Create User → Bedrock Access](https://aws.amazon.com/bedrock/)
- **Twilio**: [console.twilio.com](https://console.twilio.com/) → Account SID + Auth Token are on the homepage

